ğŸŸ¥ 1ï¸âƒ£ Brute Force (O(nÂ²)) âŒ

Idea
  Try every possible pair
  Mark used elements

âŒ Too slow for n = 10âµ


ğŸŸ¨ 2ï¸âƒ£ Better (Sorting + Two Pointers) âœ…
Idea
  Sort the array
  Use two pointers:
  l â†’ smallest
  r â†’ largest
  Compare nums[l] + nums[r] with k

class Solution {
public:
    int maxOperations(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int l = 0, r = nums.size() - 1;
        int count = 0;

        while (l < r) {
            int sum = nums[l] + nums[r];

            if (sum == k) {
                count++;
                l++;
                r--;
            }
            else if (sum < k) {
                l++;
            }
            else {
                r--;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};
